<details><summary>Add JSON parse error handling</summary>

___

**Add a <code>try...catch</code> block to the <code>parseJsonResponse</code> function to gracefully handle <br>malformed JSON responses and prevent unhandled exceptions.**

[consuelo-extension/src/services/api.ts [54-72]](https://github.com/kokayicobb/consuelo_on_call_coaching/pull/788/files#diff-8acad936aa6a6fc1d0b1ec8c453a06a4cea9d981687646b98fbacc504e149418R54-R72)

```diff
 async function parseJsonResponse<T extends { success: boolean; error?: string }>(
   response: Response,
   fallbackError: string,
   endpoint?: string,
 ): Promise<T> {
   // Capture HTTP errors (4xx/5xx) to Sentry
   if (!response.ok && endpoint) {
     captureHttpError(endpoint, response.status, {
       fallbackError,
       responseType: response.headers.get('content-type'),
     });
   }

   const contentType = response.headers.get('content-type');
   if (contentType?.includes('application/json')) {
-    return response.json() as Promise<T>;
+    try {
+      return await response.json() as T;
+    } catch {
+      return { success: false, error: fallbackError } as T;
+    }
   }
   return { success: false, error: fallbackError } as T;
 }
```



